cons:
As the review title mentions:
- weak leadership (they lack motivational skills and sometimes even people skills, professionalism, technical skills are also severely lacking);
- unrealistic expectations (top management submits unrealistic budgets to group and when they don't deliver, heads fall among sales and operational, top performers "heads" who "milked" their clients to the limit);
- speculative approach in customer relationships and lack of follow-up;
- low quality in delivery (6 out of 10 Perm consultants have no idea what they're doing and mostly wait for applicants);
- promises for raises or other benefits that don't happen or, if they do, it's often more than 1 year later;
- unaccountable management (actions taken due to their request or following their approval impact operational staff; if things go south, amnesia suddenly sets in for all managers);
- high turnover due to huge amounts of pressure.
